## Fields Per Ad

```python
class ScrapedAd(BaseModel):
    ad_library_id:      str             # Meta's ad identifier — required
    competitor:         str             # required
    primary_text:       Optional[str]   # required OR headline must be present
    headline:           Optional[str]
    description:        Optional[str]
    cta_button:         Optional[str]
    platform:           Optional[str]
    ad_format:          Optional[str]
    is_active:          bool = True
    raw_html:           str             # always stored for re-parsing
    scraped_at:         str             # ISO 8601
    carousel_id:        Optional[str]   # set when extracted from carousel
    calibration_quality: Optional[str]  # None until annotated: "low"/"medium"/"high"
    calibration_score:  Optional[float] # None until calibration runs
```

`primary_text` OR `headline` must be present — if both are None the ad is skipped.

---

## Edge Case Handling

```
Image-only ads     → skip, log event="scraper_skip", reason="no_copy_text"
Non-English ads    → detect via langdetect; skip, log reason="non_english"
                     if detection raises exception → keep the ad (default to include)
Video ads          → include with calibration_note="video_ad_short_copy"
Carousel ads       → extract each card as separate ScrapedAd with shared carousel_id
```

