## Calibration CLI

After scraping, a human must annotate a minimum of 20 ads before calibration passes.

```bash
python main.py annotate --competitor princeton_review
# Presents each ad, prompts for: low / medium / high / skip
# Saves annotation to calibration_quality field in reference_ads table

python main.py calibrate --min-annotated 20
# Runs judge against all annotated ads, checks agreement rate
# Outputs: PASS / ADJUST [dimension] / HALT
```

### Calibration Bands

```python
CALIBRATION_BANDS = {
    "low":    (0.0, 6.0),   # exclusive upper bound
    "medium": (6.0, 7.5),
    "high":   (7.5, 10.0),
}
```

### Pass Criteria

```
Agreement ≥ 75%  → PASS — proceed to generation
Agreement 50–74% → ADJUST — identify failing dimensions, update anchors, rerun
Agreement < 50%  → HALT — rubric requires fundamental revision before continuing
```

