## Test Specification

### `tests/unit/test_scraper.py`

```
Ad usability filter
- ad with primary_text → is_usable=True
- ad with only headline, no primary_text → is_usable=True
- ad with neither primary_text nor headline → is_usable=False
- is_usable=False → skip logged with reason="no_copy_text"

Language detection
- English primary_text → is_english=True
- Spanish primary_text → is_english=False
- non-English ad → skip logged with reason="non_english"
- langdetect exception on detection → defaults to is_english=True (keep)

ScrapedAd model validation
- ad with ad_library_id and competitor and primary_text → valid
- ad missing ad_library_id → ValidationError
- ad missing competitor → ValidationError
- calibration_quality defaults to None
- calibration_score defaults to None

Calibration score band classification (CALIBRATION_BANDS)
- score 5.9 → "low"  (exclusive upper bound at 6.0)
- score 6.0 → "medium" (inclusive lower bound)
- score 7.4 → "medium"
- score 7.5 → "high" (inclusive lower bound)
- score 7.6 → "high"

Calibration pass rate thresholds
- 16 correct out of 20 annotated = 0.80 → PASS
- 15 correct out of 20 annotated = 0.75 → PASS (boundary — inclusive)
- 14 correct out of 20 annotated = 0.70 → ADJUST
- 10 correct out of 20 annotated = 0.50 → HALT (boundary)
- 9  correct out of 20 annotated = 0.45 → HALT
- fewer than min_annotated_ads=20 → raises CalibrationError before running
```

